   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>B. The Ammonites Taking the Land of Gad</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>The Ammonites took the land of Gad and possessed it with their god Malcam Jer 49:1 .</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>C. Jehovah Causing War against the Ammonites</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>Jeremiah 49:2a and 3 tell us that Jehovah would cause war against the Ammonites.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Their nation would become a mound of desolation, and its villages would be burned with fire.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>Their god Malcam would go into exile together with its priests and its princes.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>D. Israel Dispossessing Those Who Dispossess Him</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>Regarding the Ammonites, we are told that Israel will dispossess those who dispossess him v. 2b; cf.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Zeph 2:8-9; Amos 1:13-15 .</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>E. Jehovah Turning Again</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>the Captivity of the Children of Ammon</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>Jeremiah 49:6 prophesies that afterward Jehovah will turn again the captivity of the children of Ammon.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>V. JEHOVAH'S PUNISHMENT</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>AND JUDGMENT UPON EDOM</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>The word in 49:7-22 concerns Jehovah's punishment and judgment upon Edom.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>A. A Nation Typifying the World</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>of the Old and Fleshly Man Who Struggles</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>against the God-chosen and Spiritual People</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>Edom was a nation of the descendants of Esau, who was the twin brother of Jacob; who was hated by God and destined by God to serve his younger brother; and who was struggling in the flesh against his brother Gen 36:9; 25:21-26a; Mal 1:3a; Rom 9:13b; 1 Kings 11:14-16; 2 Kings 8:20, 22; Psa 83:4-6; 137:7; Num 20:21 .</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>As such a nation, Edom typifies the world of the old and fleshly man who struggles against the God-chosen and spiritual people.</S>
   </TEXT>
